result.execSummary:
The defendant Bradley J. Sutek was found guilty of the following charge(s) in this case.

  • Illegal Shining of Deer, Elk, or Bear, an unclassified misdemeanor, Wisconsin Statutes 29.314(3)(a).

Notice to employers: It may be a violation of state law to discriminate against a job applicant because of an arrest or conviction record. Generally speaking, an employer may refuse to hire an applicant on the basis of a conviction only if the circumstances of the conviction substantially relate to the particular job. For more information, see Wisconsin Statute 111.335 and the Department of Workforce Development's publication, Arrest and Conviction Records under the Law.

supervisions.notes: All financial obligations to be paid at the rate of $100/month by wage assignment commencing 6-1-16 or serve 60 days jail and civil judgment to be entered.

All items seized under tag A50810 are forfeited to the State.
Remington Rifle, Thunder Hawk Crossbow with scope, 4 Crossbow bolts and 25-06 ammunition.
